Examples
              * The  following  command writes out an SDF 2.1 compliant output
                file named my.sdf with  4  digits  after  the  decimal  point:
                write_sdf -version 2.1 -precision 4 my.sdf

              * The  following  example SDF files compare the output of -edges
                edged to the output of -edges noedge.

                Resultant SDF with -edges set to edged:

                (HOLD (posedge  D)  (posedge  CK)  (-0.14:-0.14:-0.14))  (HOLD
                (negedge  D) (posedge CK) (-0.06:-0.06:-0.06)) (SETUP (posedge
                D) (posedge CK) (0.22:0.22:0.22)) (SETUP (negedge D)  (posedge
                CK) (0.41:0.41:0.41))

                With  -edges  set  to  noedge  only the edge specifiers of the
                clock pin are written.

                (HOLD D (posedge CK) (-0.14:-0.06:-0.06))  (SETUP  D  (posedge
                CK) (0.22:0.41:0.41))

